  "local_port": 43560,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How can I retrieve my WeChat account if I've forgotten my password, I just linked my linked & I remember I wechat ID.But I don't have QQ/phone linked?",
  "response": "Recovering your WeChat account without access to a linked phone number or QQ account is challenging, but if you remember your WeChat ID and have an email address linked to your account, you can follow these steps to regain access:\n\n### **1. Reset Your Password via Email**\n\n**a. Open the WeChat App:**\n- Launch WeChat on your smartphone or access the WeChat PC/Mac application.\n\n**b. Navigate to the Login Screen:**\n- On the login page, tap on **\"Forgot Password?\"**.\n\n**c. Choose the Email Reset Option:**\n- Select the option to reset your password using your **email address**.\n\n**d. Enter Your Registered Email:**\n- Input the email address associated with your WeChat account.\n\n**e. Check Your Email:**\n- Look for a password reset email from WeChat.\n- Open the email and follow the provided instructions to create a new password.\n\n**f. Log In with the New Password:**\n- Return to the WeChat app and log in using your WeChat ID and the newly set password.\n\n### **2. If Email Is Not Linked or You Don't Receive the Reset Email**\n\nIf you didn't link an email address to your WeChat account or aren't receiving the reset email, proceed with the following steps:\n\n**a. Visit WeChat\u2019s Official Support Page:**\n- Go to the [WeChat Help Center](https://help.wechat.com/) using a web browser.\n\n**b. Submit a Support Ticket:**\n- Look for the option to **\"Contact Support\"** or **\"Submit a Request\"**.\n- Fill out the necessary details, including your WeChat ID, and explain that you've forgotten your password and don't have access to a linked phone number or QQ account.\n\n**c. Provide Verification Information:**\n- Be prepared to provide additional information to verify your identity, such as:\n  - The email address associated with the account.\n  - Details about when you created the account.\n  - Any previous login information or devices you've used with the account.\n\n**d. Await Support Response:**\n- WeChat Support will review your request and guide you through the recovery process. This may take a few business days.\n\n### **3. Additional Tips**\n\n- **Keep Personal Information Handy:** Ensure you have any personal information that can prove ownership of the account ready, such as screenshots of the account, transaction history, or any linked services.\n\n- **Check Spam/Junk Folders:** Sometimes, password reset emails might end up in the spam or junk folders of your email account. Make sure to check these folders if you don't see the email in your inbox.\n\n- **Secure Your Email Account:** Ensure that the email linked to your WeChat is secure and that you have access to it, as this is crucial for the recovery process.\n\n- **Enable Two-Factor Authentication (Once Recovered):** To prevent future access issues, consider linking a phone number or QQ account to your WeChat and enabling two-factor authentication for added security.\n\n### **4. Preventive Measures for the Future**\n\n- **Link Multiple Recovery Options:** Always link both a phone number and an email address to your WeChat account to provide multiple recovery pathways.\n\n- **Regularly Update Recovery Information:** Ensure that your linked email and phone number are up-to-date to facilitate easier recovery if needed.\n\n- **Use a Password Manager:** Consider using a password manager to securely store and manage your WeChat password and other important credentials.\n\nBy following these steps, you should be able to recover your WeChat account even without access to a linked phone number or QQ account. If you encounter any issues during the process, persistent communication with WeChat Support is key to resolving the problem.\n\n---\n\n**Useful Links:**\n- [WeChat Help Center](https://help.wechat.com/)\n- [WeChat Official Support (via App)](https://support.wechat.com/)\n\nIf you need more specific assistance, feel free to ask!",
